      "content": "The comforting myth of American meritocracy is nothing more than a sophisticated smokescreen designed to obscure the brutal reality of systemic racism. Proponents of \"equal opportunity\" willfully ignore that the starting line is not level; it is a chasm carved out by centuries of discriminatory policy and wealth hoarding. To pretend that hard work alone can overcome inherited economic sabotage is not just naive—it is a deliberate ideological defense of entrenched white supremacy. Therefore, only radical wealth redistribution can dismantle the structural violence baked into our economic system.",
